how it related to other presentations Innis made in Britain during the same period. It explores how Innis sought to enrich his analysis by incorporating material related to phenomena such as war, education, religion, culture, geography, and finance. An insightful foreword by Marshall McLuhan is included, as well as bibliographical references and a revised index. By providing a narrative based on extensive notes from Innis, this edition makes Empire and Communications more accessible and contributes to the broad efforts to shape Innis’s legacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aCommunicationxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aEmpire and Communication.  aGraeco-Roman civilization.  aHarold A. Innis.  aMarshall McLuhan.  aMary Q. Innis.  aalphabet.  acommunications.  amedia history.  amedia studies.  aorality.  apower structures.  aprinting.  awriting.1 aBuxton, William J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuxton, William J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aInnis, Harold A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnis, Mary Q., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLuhan, Marshall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z